1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
A green build is not a shippable game. PlayReceipt is an evidence gate for AI-built games.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
It returns Pass, Repair, Human Review, or Unverified—never one flattering synthetic score.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:32,000
The real snapshot completed 2,000 seeded runs with zero crashes and zero stalls.

4
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:45,000
But weak strategy, missing reduced motion, and no human calibration keep it at Repair.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Now the judge can paste a new JSON evidence bundle with no account and issue a receipt.

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The result is exact, copyable, downloadable, and capped at a Human Review boundary.

7
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:20,000
The trail shows Ingest, Judge, Repair Plan, and where automation must stop.

8
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:32,000
The browser, API, CLI, and GitHub Action all call the same deterministic audit engine.

9
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Repair and Unverified fail CI. Human Review stays successful with a visible warning.

10
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Eleven regression tests cover adapter parity and abuse boundaries with zero runtime dependencies.

11
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Codex and GPT-5.6 shaped the product contract, implementation, tests, and browser verification.

12
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:11,300
Try your own evidence, then inspect every claim in the public repository.
